OL,3,CBroadcasting: questions for the
OL,4,Cpolitical parties
OL,6,GThose of us who care about
OL,7,Gbroadcasting should not be afraid to
OL,8,Gask candidates questions about it
OL,9,Gduring the election campaign.
OL,11,FIt may be of less concern to many than
OL,12,Fgovernment competency, the cost of
OL,13,Fliving and the quality of public
OL,14,Fservices.
OL,16,FBut it matters to the whole of society
OL,17,Fall the same.
OL,19,FThe last 5 years saw the government
OL,20,Fadd to the pressure on BBC funding by
OL,21,Freneging on an agreement on licence
OL,22,Ffee increases.
