OL,6,FSome may be more concerned about the
OL,7,Fimpact on commercial radio. It will be
OL,8,Fmuch easier for stations to change
OL,9,Ftheir formats or drop local output as
OL,10,Flong as local news is maintained.
OL,12,FBut the big question in this campaign
OL,13,Fis about the future of the BBC.
OL,15,FWhat role should it play and how
OL,16,Fshould it be funded?
OL,18,FThe Conservatives had previously
OL,19,Findicated the TV licence was on the
OL,20,Fway out but, of course, finding a
OL,21,Fviable and practical alternative is
OL,22,Feasier said than done.
