OL,6,FAnd lastly what about Freeview itself?
OL,7,FHowever technology may develop and
OL,8,Fregardless of whether the internet-
OL,9,Fbased Freely service takes off, what
OL,10,Fshould the government do?
OL,12,FAt the very least should there be an
OL,13,Fexplicit long-term commitment to
OL,14,Fmaintaining Freeview as a "service of
OL,15,Flast resort" to ensure the potentially
OL,16,Fvulnerable do not lose out?
OL,18,FOr can a government produce a grand
OL,19,Fvision which could lead to every home
OL,20,Fhaving unmetered, reliable internet
OL,21,Faccess?
